08/10/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Council of Europe (CoE) Secretary General Walter Schwimmer urged voters to take part in the 19 October national referendum on revising the constitution. In a speech to a special session of parliament Tuesday (7 October), he described the referendum as "the final test of Romania's democratic maturity". The session was devoted to the 10th anniversary of Romania's entry into the CoE.
In other news, British Minister for Europe Denis McShane visited Bucharest and pledged support for Romania's efforts to complete accession talks with the EU in 2004, with the aim of becoming a full-fledged member of the Union in 2007. To that end, he urged Romania to step up efforts to implement key reforms. (Mediafax, Rompres - 07/10/03)
